The standard way to represent a signal made of 4 symbols is by using 2 bits/symbol, but the 
entropy of the source is 1.73 bits/symbol. If this Huffman code is used to represent the signal, then the average length is lowered to 1.83 bits/symbol; it is still far from the theoretical limit because the probabilities of the symbols are different from negative powers of two.
